		<title>19HOPES AND FEARS OF CHILDREN</title>
		<content> The following is a list of hopes and  
 fears written by class of 9year olds. 
   More playing places for children.   
  No more World wars,no more famine.   
   Computerized schooling.             
  A sports centre in Ludlow.           
   Trains will still stop at Ludlow    
 station.                              
  Books don't die out.                 
   No more hooligans.                  
  People eat food and not pills.       
   Lovely views are not spoiled by ugly
 buildings.                            
  The world is not taken over by       
 computers.                            
  When I finish school there will be a 
 job for me.                           
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       </content>
